  The production of tropical crops developed steadily. In 
1993, the areas sown to tropical crops in the whole province 
amounted to 44.17 hectares, basically maintaining the level of 
the previous year. There was a rapid increase in the output of 
rubber and dry rubber, coconuts, and binlang [apples]. Output 
of major tropical crops was as follows: 


