  In 1993, afforested area in the whole province amounted to 
29,800 hectares, basically maintaining the level of the previous 
year. 
  There was rapid development in the production of animal 
husbandry. The number of pigs, oxen, and sheep all increased 
compared with the previous year. There was a rapid increase in 
the output of meat, poultry, and eggs. Output of major animal 
products and the amount of livestock were as follows: 


