  Production and sales of industrial products were linked with 
satisfaction, and there were major improvements in enterprise 
economic performance. In 1993, the output of industrial sales 
at the township level and above in the whole province totalled 
8.148 billion yuan, an increase of 33.6 percent over the 
previous year, the rate of sales of industrial products was 93.3 
percent, and the composite indicator of industrial economic 
performance was 86.8 percent, an increase of 11.4 percentage 
points over the previous year. Profits and taxes realized by 
independent accounting industries in the whole province amounted 
to 692 million yuan, an increase of 34.2 percent over the 
previous year. Profits and taxes realized by an average of 
every 100-yuan sales income rose from 8.16 yuan of the previous 
year to 8.83 yuan. Profits and taxes realized by an average of 
every 100-yuan funds rose from 5.76 yuan of the previous year to 
6.25 yuan, and annual turnover of floating funds was 1.35 times. 
  The building industry developed rapidly. In 1993, the added 
value of building industry in the whole province totalled 3.367 
billion yuan, an increase of 72.7 over the previous year, 
accounting for 16.5 percent of the gross domestic product (GDP). 
At the end of 1993, there were 467 building enterprises at or 
above the township and town level in the whole province, the 
area of houses under construction in the whole year amounted to 
9.418 million square meters, an increase of 41.9 percent over 
the previous year, the rate of fine quality projects was 52.5 
percent, and the total amount of profits and taxes delivered to 
higher authorities was 105.1 million yuan, an increase of 45.1 
percent over that of the previous year. 
  There was some progress in geological surveying work, six 
places of industrial mineral deposits were newly discovered or 
proven, and 46,400 meters of core drilling were completed. 
<H5>  III. Fixed Asset Investments </H5>
  Fixed asset investments grew by a big margin. In 1993, fixed 
asset investment in Hainan Province reached 16.938 billion yuan, 
an increase of 94.6 percent over the previous year, in which 
collective ownership units fulfilled 340 million yuan, up by 
98.7 percent, individuals in urban and rural areas fulfilled 897 
million yuan, up by 51.5 percent, and state-owned units and 
other economic-type enterprises fulfilled 15.701 billion yuan, 
up by 97.7 percent. In the investments fulfilled by state-owned 
units and other economic enterprises, state-owned units 
fulfilled 7.164 billion yuan, shareholding enterprises fulfilled 
3.480 billion yuan, foreign-funded enterprises fulfilled 1.109 
billion yuan, and enterprises financed by Hong Kong, Macao, and 
Taiwan businesses fulfilled 1.475 billion yuan. 
  In 1993, capital construction investments in the whole 
province reached 8.966 billion yuan, an increase of 1.07 times 
over the previous year, and primary industry reached 372 million 
yuan, up by 20.9 percent, secondary industry reached 2.615 
billion yuan, an increase of 1.23 times, and tertiary industry 
reached 5.979 billion yuan, an increase of 1.10 times. In the 
amount of investments made by capital construction in the whole 
province, energy industry fulfilled an investment of 653 million 
yuan, an increase of 1.12 times over the previous year, and 
communications and telecommunications fulfilled an investment of 
2.296 billion yuan, an increase of 2.37 times over the previous 
year. The proportion of investments in energy, communications, 
and telecommunications in capital construction rose from 22.8 
percent the previous year to 32.9 percent. 
  In 1993, capital construction appropriations in the whole 
province reached 9.455 billion yuan, in which funds raised by 
localities and enterprises occupied 40.9 percent, use of foreign 
investments 14.1 percent, domestic loans 22.4 percent, state 
budgetary funds 3.8 percent, and other funds 18.8 percent. 
  The pace of renovation and transformation quickened. In 
1993, renovation and transformation in the whole province 
fulfilled an investment of 929 million yuan, an increase of 74.8 
percent over the previous year, in which investments for 
increasing production capacity amounted to 380 million yuan, 
accounting for 40.9 percent, and investments for increasing 
varieties and improving products quality amounted to 202 million 
yuan, accounting for 21.7 percent. 
  The momentum of investments in commodity flats did not slow 
down. In 1993, commodity flats in the whole province fulfilled 
an investment of 5.753 billion yuan, an increase of 90.4 percent 
over the previous year; the area of commodity flats under 
construction totalled 7.522 million square meters, an increase 
of 49.3 percent over the previous year, and the area under new 
construction this year totalled 4,273,100 square meters. The 
area of commodity flats completed totalled 697,200 square 
meters, a reduction of 34.3 percent from the previous year, and 
the area of commodity flat sales totalled 460,400 square meters, 
a reduction of 67.4 percent. 
  Construction of key projects and large and medium-sized 
projects made major progress. In 1993, the shareholding system 
was carried out in building Fenghuang Airport, the east line 
expressway, Nanshan power plant, and other key projects, which 
effectively collected funds and quickened the pace of 
construction. By the end of 1993, the principal part of 
Fenghuang Airport project, the Huangzhu- Lingshui section of the 
east line expressway, and the civil engineering project of 
Nanshan power plant were basically completed. The first Daguang 
Dam 60,000-kilowatt unit was linked with the power generation 
network, and several post and telecommunications projects were 
completed and made available to the users. The Hainan Iron and 
Steel Plant, Hainan Cold-Rolled Steel Sheet Plant, Hainan 
Silicon Chip Factory, Hainan Jindao Plywood Factory, Haikou Cord 
Fabric Factory, Haikou Polyamide Fiber Factory, Lingshui Wool 
Top and Blankets Factory, Haikou pipeline gas, and other 
projects were under full construction. 
  In 1993 the area of buildings under construction in the 
whole 
province totalled 15,200,100 square meters, of which residential 
flats accounted for 7,841,400 square meters. The area of 
buildings completed totalled 5,209,400 square meters, of which 
residential flats accounted for 3,660,700 square meters, 
investments by collectives and individuals in urban and rural 
areas not included. Newly increased fixed assets in the whole 
province totalled 5.07 billion yuan, and the rate of fixed 
assets made available to the users was 32.3 percent. 
  In 1993, the newly increased major production capacity in 
the 
whole province included: An installed hydraulic capacity of 
66,000 kwh; 140 kilometers of 220,000 kva transmission and 
transformer lines; newly built highways of 25 kilometers; 
rebuilt highway of 37 kilometers; 12 newly built individual 
highway bridges; two airplanes leased by financing; purchased 
ships of 11,200 tonnage; long distance telecommunications cable 
lines of 178.1 extended kilometers; an annual production of wine 
and liquor of 5,895 tons; 340,000 tons of cement; and 50,000 
tire inner tubes; 700 tons of raw materials processed per day 
for machine-made sugar; a grain storehouse storage capacity of 
49,500 tons; primary and secondary schools seats of 58,000; a 
daily supply of running water in cities reached 50,000 tons; 
four permanent bridges in cities, and extensions of city roads 
reaching 36 kilometers. 
<H5>  IV. Transportation, Post, and Telecommunications </H5>
  Development of transportation, post, and telecommunications 
quickened. In 1993, the added value of transportation and post 
and telecommunications in the whole province totalled 1.262 
billion yuan, an increase of 26.7 percent over the previous 
year, in which the added value of communications and 
transportation amounted to 986 million yuan, an increase of 17.3 
percent. The added value of post and telecommunications 
totalled 276 million yuan, up by 70.2 percent. The situation of 
various transportation volumes fulfilled was as follows: 


